        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2869596020" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1556487017968207334">This book was weird. I picked it up at a used book store that was all but sold out of Stephen King novels. I had never read a John Saul book before, but decided to give it a try for the low price of 50 cents. I&apos;m glad I did, honestly. Despite the mediocre rating, the book was good. The writing style was good and the story was interesting. The characters were well thought out, but the believability among some of their actions just wasn&apos;t that high - of course the recently divorced detective devel</span>
  <span id="freeText1556487017968207334" style="display:none">This book was weird. I picked it up at a used book store that was all but sold out of Stephen King novels. I had never read a John Saul book before, but decided to give it a try for the low price of 50 cents. I'm glad I did, honestly. Despite the mediocre rating, the book was good. The writing style was good and the story was interesting. The characters were well thought out, but the believability among some of their actions just wasn't that high - of course the recently divorced detective develops a crush on our reporter protagonist, so scandalous. But the PLOT. The PLOT is the reason for the rating. The book was so interesting until the plot really started unraveling. Then it just turned downright weird and unbelievable. But it was a good read, especially if you are into paranormal (what that be how to describe this?) crime thrillers.</span>
  <a data-text-id="1556487017968207334" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
