<div id="review_3405955270" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3405955270" />
    <a title="Levi J. Miller" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/108397959-levi-j-miller"><img alt="Levi J. Miller" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1594510242p2/108397959.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3405955270?book_show_action=true">Jul 05, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Levi J. Miller" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Levi J. Miller" href="/user/show/108397959-levi-j-miller">Levi J. Miller</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3405955270" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer6571533669391527314">First off, this book was a breeze to get through, and it’s for this reason that I’ll most likely read at least a few more of Saul’s novels. If you’re used to writing as dense as Stephen King’s, then this is casual reading. This isn’t a bad thing, but you should know going into this book that the writing is quite straightforward and easy to digest. <br/><br/>The mix of a supernatural story and a serial killer thriller was pretty interesting, I was captivated for its entirety. My only big gripe that keeps t</span>
  <span id="freeText6571533669391527314" style="display:none">First off, this book was a breeze to get through, and it’s for this reason that I’ll most likely read at least a few more of Saul’s novels. If you’re used to writing as dense as Stephen King’s, then this is casual reading. This isn’t a bad thing, but you should know going into this book that the writing is quite straightforward and easy to digest. <br /><br />The mix of a supernatural story and a serial killer thriller was pretty interesting, I was captivated for its entirety. My only big gripe that keeps this book from getting a 5-star rating is it’s ending, which is pretty much what you expect, and doesn’t really resolve much other than what it absolutely needs to. <br /><br />Still, I really enjoyed this and up until the last few pages it was very gripping throughout. Excited to read more of John Saul’s books!</span>
  <a data-text-id="6571533669391527314" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


