<div id="review_3215978850" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/3215978850" />
    <a title="Kristy Schreurs" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/44636250-kristy-schreurs"><img alt="Kristy Schreurs" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1540452010p2/44636250.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3215978850?book_show_action=true">Mar 03, 2020</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kristy Schreurs" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kristy Schreurs" href="/user/show/44636250-kristy-schreurs">Kristy Schreurs</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="really liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">really liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3215978850" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer13240170007932642515">I power read a bunch of John Saul this week as I was under the weather. This one was different from the others I had picked up. It didn&apos;t focus on creepy children but instead on a journalist Anne Jeffers who helped put &quot;The Experimenter&quot; to death for his heinous crimes. Only upon his death in the electric chair the killings start again. Meanwhile her husband suffers a massive heart attack and she struggles with a change in his persona after his attack. Without giving anything away I loved the tw</span>
  <span id="freeText13240170007932642515" style="display:none">I power read a bunch of John Saul this week as I was under the weather. This one was different from the others I had picked up. It didn't focus on creepy children but instead on a journalist Anne Jeffers who helped put "The Experimenter" to death for his heinous crimes. Only upon his death in the electric chair the killings start again. Meanwhile her husband suffers a massive heart attack and she struggles with a change in his persona after his attack. Without giving anything away I loved the twist in this book. Dark and intriguing. I only took one star off because I have issues with detailed animal abuse or pet killings in novels and this one has one scene I had to skip through 3 pages or so of. Could have done without that. Still enjoyed the book though. </span>
  <a data-text-id="13240170007932642515" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
